This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of reinforcement learning and value distribution in approximating optimal policies. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of an algorithm for decision-making. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as reinforcement learning is commonly used in robotics applications. It may also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves the control of an agent in an environment. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves the use of quantile regression to estimate value distributions.
